{
  "patterns": [
    {
      "id": "comparison-table",
      "name": "Comparison Table",
      "keywords": ["difference", "vs", "compare", "versus", "comparison", "distinguish"],
      "priority": 10,
      "structure": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "table",
            "required": true,
            "format": "table",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "min-columns", "value": 2 },
              { "type": "has-headers", "value": true },
              { "type": "feature-column", "value": true }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "rules": [],
        "template": "| Feature | Item A | Item B |\n|---------|--------|--------|\n| ... | ... | ... |",
        "examples": [
          "**Question:** What's the difference between REST and GraphQL?\n\n**Answer:**\n| Feature | REST | GraphQL |\n|---------|------|---------|"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "definition",
      "name": "Definition",
      "keywords": ["what is", "define", "explain what", "definition of"],
      "priority": 9,
      "structure": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "definition-sentence",
            "required": true,
            "format": "text",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "single-sentence", "value": true },
              { "type": "followed-by-blank-line", "value": true }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "key-characteristics",
            "required": true,
            "format": "list",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "min-items", "value": 3 },
              { "type": "max-items", "value": 5 },
              { "type": "bulleted", "value": true }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "use-cases",
            "required": false,
            "format": "list"
          },
          {
            "name": "example",
            "required": false,
            "format": "text"
          }
        ],
        "rules": [],
        "template": "A [concept] is [one-sentence definition].\n\n**Key Characteristics:**\n- Point 1\n- Point 2\n- Point 3",
        "examples": [
          "**Question:** What is a Microservice?\n\n**Answer:**\nA microservice is an independently deployable service that focuses on a single business capability.\n\n**Key Characteristics:**\n- Independently deployable and scalable"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "list",
      "name": "List-Based Answer",
      "keywords": ["types", "categories", "list", "examples of", "kinds of"],
      "priority": 8,
      "structure": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "introduction",
            "required": true,
            "format": "text",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "brief-intro", "value": true }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "list-items",
            "required": true,
            "format": "list",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "max-sentences-per-item", "value": 2 },
              { "type": "proper-syntax", "value": true },
              { "type": "allow-nesting", "value": true }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "rules": [],
        "template": "[Brief introduction]\n\n1. **Item 1**: Description\n2. **Item 2**: Description",
        "examples": [
          "**Question:** What are the SOLID principles?\n\n**Answer:**\nThe SOLID principles are five design principles for object-oriented programming:\n\n1. **Single Responsibility Principle (SRP)**: A class should have only one reason to change"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "process",
      "name": "Process/Workflow",
      "keywords": ["how to", "steps", "process", "workflow", "procedure"],
      "priority": 9,
      "structure": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "process-steps",
            "required": true,
            "format": "list",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "numbered", "value": true },
              { "type": "action-verb-start", "value": true },
              { "type": "clear-actionable", "value": true },
              { "type": "allow-nested-steps", "value": true }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "summary",
            "required": true,
            "format": "text",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "outcome-statement", "value": true }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "rules": [],
        "template": "1. **Action verb**: Description\n2. **Action verb**: Description\n\n**Result:** Outcome statement",
        "examples": [
          "**Question:** How does OAuth 2.0 authorization flow work?\n\n**Answer:**\nOAuth 2.0 authorization flow involves these steps:\n\n1. **User initiates login**: User clicks \"Login with [Provider]\""
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "code-example",
      "name": "Code Example",
      "keywords": ["implement", "code", "write", "example", "syntax", "programming"],
      "priority": 8,
      "structure": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "explanation",
            "required": true,
            "format": "text",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "before-code", "value": true }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "code-block",
            "required": true,
            "format": "code",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "fenced", "value": true },
              { "type": "language-identifier", "value": true },
              { "type": "proper-indentation", "value": true },
              { "type": "inline-comments", "value": true }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "alternative-approaches",
            "required": false,
            "format": "code",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "clearly-labeled", "value": true }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "rules": [],
        "template": "[Brief explanation]\n\n```language\ncode here\n```",
        "examples": [
          "**Question:** How do you implement a singleton pattern in Python?\n\n**Answer:**\nA singleton ensures only one instance of a class exists. Here's the implementation:\n\n```python\nclass Singleton:\n    _instance = None\n```"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "pros-cons",
      "name": "Pros and Cons",
      "keywords": ["pros", "cons", "advantages", "disadvantages", "benefits", "drawbacks"],
      "priority": 9,
      "structure": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "advantages",
            "required": true,
            "format": "list",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "header", "value": "## Advantages" },
              { "type": "bulleted", "value": true }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "disadvantages",
            "required": true,
            "format": "list",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "header", "value": "## Disadvantages" },
              { "type": "bulleted", "value": true },
              { "type": "balanced-coverage", "value": true }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "when-to-use",
            "required": false,
            "format": "text",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "header", "value": "## When to Use" }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "rules": [],
        "template": "## Advantages\n- Point 1\n- Point 2\n\n## Disadvantages\n- Point 1\n- Point 2\n\n## When to Use\nGuidance",
        "examples": [
          "**Question:** What are the pros and cons of NoSQL databases?\n\n**Answer:**\n\n## Advantages\n- **Scalability**: Horizontal scaling across multiple servers"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "architecture",
      "name": "Architecture/Diagram",
      "keywords": ["architecture", "design", "system", "diagram", "structure", "flow"],
      "priority": 8,
      "structure": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "text-explanation",
            "required": true,
            "format": "text",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "before-diagram", "value": true }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "mermaid-diagram",
            "required": true,
            "format": "diagram",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "mermaid-syntax", "value": true },
              { "type": "max-nodes", "value": 12 },
              { "type": "appropriate-type", "value": true }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "component-description",
            "required": true,
            "format": "text",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "after-diagram", "value": true }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "rules": [],
        "template": "[Text explanation]\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    A --> B\n```\n\n**Components:**\n- Component A: Description",
        "examples": [
          "**Question:** Explain the MVC architecture pattern.\n\n**Answer:**\nMVC (Model-View-Controller) separates application logic into three interconnected components:\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    User[User] --> View[View]\n```"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "troubleshooting",
      "name": "Troubleshooting/Debugging",
      "keywords": ["debug", "troubleshoot", "error", "fix", "problem", "issue"],
      "priority": 8,
      "structure": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "problem",
            "required": true,
            "format": "text",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "header", "value": "## Problem" }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "causes",
            "required": true,
            "format": "list",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "header", "value": "## Common Causes" },
              { "type": "bulleted", "value": true }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "solutions",
            "required": true,
            "format": "list",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "header", "value": "## Debugging Steps" },
              { "type": "numbered", "value": true },
              { "type": "ordered-by-likelihood", "value": true }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "prevention",
            "required": false,
            "format": "list",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "header", "value": "## Prevention" }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "rules": [],
        "template": "## Problem\n[Description]\n\n## Common Causes\n- Cause 1\n\n## Debugging Steps\n1. Step 1\n\n## Prevention\n- Tip 1",
        "examples": [
          "**Question:** How do you debug a memory leak in Node.js?\n\n**Answer:**\n\n## Problem\nMemory usage continuously increases"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "best-practices",
      "name": "Best Practices",
      "keywords": ["best practices", "guidelines", "recommendations", "tips"],
      "priority": 7,
      "structure": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "practices-list",
            "required": true,
            "format": "list",
            "constraints": [
              { "type": "numbered", "value": true },
              { "type": "prioritized", "value": true },
              { "type": "bold-title", "value": true },
              { "type": "includes-rationale", "value": true },
              { "type": "min-items", "value": 5 },
              { "type": "max-items", "value": 8 }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "rules": [],
        "template": "1. **Practice Title**: Description and rationale\n   - Additional detail\n2. **Practice Title**: Description and rationale",
        "examples": [
          "**Question:** What are API security best practices?\n\n**Answer:**\n\n1. **Use HTTPS everywhere**: Encrypt all data in transit to prevent man-in-the-middle attacks"
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
}
